GM to Cut 1,200 Jobs at German Bochum Plant, Rheinische Reports

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-03-17T23:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/gm-to-cut-1-200-jobs-at-german-bochum-plant-rheinische-reports.html
  General Motors Co. (GM)  plans to cut
1,200 jobs at its Opel plant in Bochum,  Germany , and will give
workers notice May 1,  Rheinische Post  said in a preview of an
article that will be published tomorrow, citing the local works
council.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  